<Content>Senator gran Via: reserve room 602 again for us! We spent only two nights at the splendid Senator Gran Via from Feb 01st to 03rd. The Hotel, which is really in the middle of the city, offers all what you want for a relaxing time. Once you enter the property, the staff seems to say: relax yourself, we will take care of you. No one rushs and indeed check in takes few minutes more than we are used to in big hotels... but you are on holiday, you do have time. It was quite hard finding the way to our room. Our spanish is terrible, I didn' want to speak English, my partner is Italian.... so a real mixture, but at the end we found our wonderfull, well appointed and clean smelling room with a lovely balcony over the Gran Via. We were booked on accommodation only but, probably as it was our anniversary, we had complimentary breakfast for the two days (one of with room service!). This was a great touch and I must say the offer for breakfast is something not to be missed with plenty of choice of sweets and sours and fresh fruits and what else you can eat. We had such a lovely one only once in our life when we stayed at Four Points Sheraton in Kuwait (but that costed a fortune!!).A great plus is the free bar and safe in the room, but most of all the iron board that I really had to use for my shirts.Beds are extremelly confortable and so big to allocate at least 4 people. A system to moove the bed will help to find the best position for you. They also offer a pillow menu, that we did't use as the pillow was as long as the bed is and this was perfect.Front desk staff is charming and were very helpfull when I had to receive a 18 pages fax with our flight tickets. Same for the restaurant staff and the cleaning lady who used to greet us anytime during the day. We really cannot express how we already miss this lovely hotel and already planning an other week end, not so far away. Please save room 602 for us. Mr  Mrs Moccia 
