<Author>Mojito82
<Content>A Good Property in a Great Location My wife, ten year old son and I just returned from a five night stay in Madrid. The Senator Gran Via was a perfectly located base for our touring on foot and was within walking distance of most sites.Notwithstanding our request for a quiet room on a higher floor, we were allocated a room on the second floor overlooking the very busy street in front of the hotel. Having arrived late and looking forward to settling in, I never questioned this oversight. In hindsight, it made little difference. The double glazed windows with an additional wooden shutter blocked virtually all street noise and we slept well in comfortable twin beds with comforters. Our son had a pull out bed in an adjacent space with sliding doors dividing the room. The free mini bar was a welcome perk and the breakfast was very good.Although the staff were pleasant enough, we were a little surprised at their lack of definitive advice about the surrounding restaurants and touring options. They were frank in saying that they had no opinions about certain topics but in the absence of a dedicated concierge service it seems that some education on matters of interest to guests would be helpful.There is a neat restaurant called Pink Sushiman around the corner (to the left) about 100 metres. Although the staff knew nothing about it, the sushi and stir fry was good and food circulates on conveyer belts by the booths in a scene right out of the Jetsons. Our ten year old loved it!The property met our expectations and the reviews we read in anticipation of our visit prepared us properly for what we found - A good European hotel in a great location. Much has been written about the proximity to a red light area. Again, I think others have accurately described how easy this is to avoid if it offends although it was pretty benign stuff . Madrid has a heavy police presence in all tourist areas.A Real Madrid football game was a highlight which we would recommend. We took an easy day trip from Atocha Station to Toledo (30 minutes by AVE train) and would recommend this to others if you have an extra day and like to walk hills (Toledo sits on a large hill). The Cathedral is stunning.We enjoyed our stay and would recommend this property. 
