<Author>KnD.Moore
<Content>Great Hotel! We stayed at the Senator Gran Via over the first weekend in July. It was booked after reading all the great reviews on Trip Advisor and we weren't disappointed.We took a taxi from Barajas airport into Madrid and can't help feeling the taxi driver took a few liberties with us. The reviews stated the trip should have cost us about 25 - 30 euros. Ours cost 35 euros plus tip and he dropped us off at the wrong hotel!Be aware if this is your first time, there are two Hotel Senators on the Gran Via. The Hotel Senator Espana and the Hotel Senator Gran Via. We didn't know this and apparently neither did the taxi driver.After a short walk along the Gran Via we arrived at our correct hotel. The staff were marvellous. Whilst I checked in another member of staff provided my family with drinks, maps and sightseeing advice.We had a room on the 2nd floor with twin electric beds and a converted sofa bed for my daughter. The room was spotlessly clean with TV, CD stereo, air conditioning and of course the now infamous free mini-bar. I must also say that the double glazing in this hotel is amazing. The Gran Via never stops but you could hardly notice the noise with the windows closed.The bathroom was a little on the small side for two adults and a teenager at times, but it was well stocked, a powerful shower, had clean towels every day and plenty of hot water.We had bed and breakfast reservations and the breakfasts were excellent. A choice of cereals, fruits, cold meats, cheeses and breads together with the option of freshly cooked omelettes.We were aware of the ladies over the road prior to our visit, but even though we tended to avoid the Calle La Montera the majority of the time, nowhere near as bad as I perceived it would be from the other reviews. We were never bothered by anyone and there is always a police presence.For the return journey to the airport, ask the hotel to book the shuttle. It only costs 6 euros per person.This is one of the best hotels we have had the fortune to stay in and were sorry to leave. We will definitely go back again when we return to Madrid. 
