<Content>Great hotel We just returned from a 1 wk. stay at this hotel. This is a great hotel  I'd stay here again. The staff is friendly, helpful,  most speak english. No problem with the reservation or room rate. The elevators are prompt  quick. The location is on Gran Via with easy access to taxis  metro stop in front of hotel. Rooms are clean  very well appointed. There isn't much they don't provide in the rooms; TV, internet, radio/CD, free (yes, free) mini bar w/sodas, water,  beer, plenty of toiletries, magnifying mirror in bath, hair dryer, electric beds, balconies w/ view of Gran Via, cold AC, ceiling fan, too much to list. The breakfast is first rate with plenty to choose from as well as short order for eggs, bacon, etc. There is a small grocery around the corner for snacks. TV is limited for english, only news  sports, but they do have pay per view for movies (13 euro). The only negative things I can say, are that the beds are a bit firm for me  pillows flat. The street to the side of the hotel, Montero, is a hooker street, but they aren't aggressive. If you opt for the shuttle to the airport, it is only 6 euro/person, but allow for at least an hour, because they pick up at another hotel too. Taxis in Madrid are small  don't accommodate more than 2-3 people  2 suitcases. We had 4 people  4 bags  had to take 2 taxis from the airport. We didn't wait in hardly any lines for any of the sites. Don't miss Monasterio Descalza Reales(only by guided tour, in Spanish), Prado museum, Parque Retiro, Thyssen-B. museum, Reina-Sofia (great Picasso exhibition, but the rest is modern),  Royal Palace  park. We took side trips to Toledo, Segovia,  El Escorial. I'd skip Toledo; the castle is closed  it is really hot  frustrating to get around. Take the bus to Segovia instead of the train; train is 2 hrs., bus is 1 hr. This is a great hotel with all the necessities. We found people in Mardrid to be friendly and helpful. 
